						<div class="postbody">I like using VirtuaNES myself, it has good graphical inferface, good sound interface, and is pretty much accurate, but not as accurate than Nintendulator or FCEUltra.
<br />
<br />About CV3, I think this is there because of the NTSC-&gt;PAL transition, and because the programmers didn't know that it was possible to write to $2005 between two $2006 writes, there is 8 black scanlines below the status bar, and where the scroll is setup to a new value varies in this 8 pixels range.</div>

					
