					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">0..340, of course.
<br />
<br />[edit]
<br />
<br />The final test is complete: the VRAM address vertical scroll increment takes place at cycle #251 - that is, during the data fetch portion of the last tile's attribute data (cycle #250 is when it outputs the attribute address). This happens to be exactly the timing my emulator currently uses. Horizontal increments have also been verified to occur during the 4th cycle of each tile (again, during the data fetch portion of the attribute data); in addition, the very last tile on each scanline increments both the vertical AND horizontal offsets - evidently, this why the PPU needs to reset the horizontal offset later.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
